Andrew D. Rebello
July 24 at 12:50 PM ·

Rising junior students and parents! S.O.A.R. (Summer Opportunities for Academic Recharge), is an online learning initiative we created to mitigate learning loss. The research is clear and compelling. Summer learning loss, or “summer slide”, can be substantial for many students and school closures can compound the problem. With the MCAS cancelled this past spring, we know our rising junior students will need to test at some point this year. Parents, check your emails for the link to sign up!

Summer learning loss, or “summer slide”, can be substantial for many students and school closures can compound the problem. With the MCAS cancelled this past spring, we know our rising junior students will need to test at some point this year. Parents, check your emails for the link to sign up!

post_text: Diman celebrated months of hard work on Friday, as faculty and students watched the installation of two Sluice Gates. Special thanks to the faculty and students in the Drafting, Carpentry, Machine Tool, Metal Fabrication & Welding programs for the contribution to the project.

post_text: True then, true now! Thank you to all of our our community partners that help Diman supply the next generation of leaders in our community!! #DimanStrong
shared_text:
Perfect Smiles
June 11, 2018 at 11:15 AM ·

Diman Regional Vocational Technical High School turns young men and women into skilled members of the community, they can't maintain that level of quality without the help of industry professionals. Dr. Miranda is an advisor to the Dental Assisting Program, where she helps steer the vocational program and students toward future success.

Diman values a diverse population of individuals on our boards, and encourages people in all levels of industry to participate.

The advisory board meets twice a year, and are critical to the continued success of the program. Dr. Maranda’s involvement on the board help keep the Dental Program up-to-date with inside knowledge of industry trends and technologies, both cutting-edge and proven industry standards.

Contributions of industry professionals like Dr. Miranda’s are what helps Diman remain the vibrant learning community we're known as.

post_text:
MIAA Board of Directors Conference Call Meeting Highlights April 24, 2020

The MIAA Board of Directors (BOD) held a conference call meeting on April 24th consisting of over 30 participants representing the BOD, MIAA staff and members of the press. Discussion was focused on the Board of Director’s response to the membership regarding the Governor’s order on Tuesday, April 21st closing all public and private schools in Massachusetts (effectively all MIAA member schools).

Motion: Cancel all 2020 spring sports and spring tournaments due to the closure of schools by Governor Baker for the remainder of the 2019-2020 school year because of the COVID-19 pandemic. (T. Arria/M. Trahan) APPROVED 16-0

At the next Board meeting, informational questions such as the ability for spring coaches to have contact with spring athletes, which have been asked for clarification to Board members, will be discussed.

The next meeting is May 13, 2020 at 12:00pm

post_text:
It is during moments like this, at a time when uncertainty and crisis surrounds all of us, that the Diman spirit and the best of humanity becomes evident.

Diman teachers Manny Botelho and Donald Travers used Diman equipment and materials to fabricate 200 face shields which were delivered to our HEROES on the front lines at Woman & Infants, and Hospice RI. We salute and thank all of the nurses, doctors, first responders, police & fire depts. for their selfless work and tremendous courage. #DimanStrong #WeAreDiman
text:
It is during moments like this, at a time when uncertainty and crisis surrounds all of us, that the Diman spirit and the best of humanity becomes evident.

Diman teachers Manny Botelho and Donald Travers used Diman equipment and materials to fabricate 200 face shields which were delivered to our HEROES on the front lines at Woman & Infants, and Hospice RI. We salute and thank all of the nurses, doctors, first responders, police & fire depts. for their selfless work and tremendous courage. #DimanStrong #WeAreDiman
